article.description: Julian Champagnie scored 14 points and grabbed 11 rebounds for his first career double-double to lead St. John's to a 79-69 win over St. Peter's on Tuesday night.
article.headline: Champagnie carries St. John's over St. Peter's 79-69
article.linkText: Champagnie carries St. John's over St. Peter's 79-69
article.story: NEW YORK -- Julian Champagnie scored 14 points and grabbed 11 rebounds for his first career double-double to lead St. John's to a 79-69 win over St. Peter's on Tuesday night. LJ Figueroa had 19 points for St. John's (7-2), which never trailed and dished a season-high 24 assists. Mustapha Heron added 17 points and Josh Roberts had eight rebounds and four blocks. Aaron Estrada scored a career-high 18 points for the Peacocks (1-4). Fousseyni Drame added 10 points and Derrick Woods grabbed seven rebounds. St. John's takes on West Virginia at home on Saturday. St. Peter's plays Fairleigh Dickinson at home next Wednesday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
